Safe Welding Area was originally approved by the Houma District on 2/2/1995. Safe Welding Area approval re-issued by the Lafayette District on 10/2/2017 to include the new name on the form and also confirmed to be in compliance during inspection offshore (MR).

The rig's rated depth for WO operations is 25,000 ft.

The rig's Safe Welding Area has mitigation conditions for SBM and OBM cuttings boxes.  Refer to approval letter attached in d-base.

Synthetic oil based drilling fluid (SBM) and diesel oil based drilling fluid (OBM) are utilized on the Hercules Rig 120. Cuttings boxes are used to contain OBM cuttings and to contain wet SBM cuttings if the SBM cuttings dryer system suffers a temporary disruption. Due to deck space limitations there is a necessity to store cutting boxes within a 35' radius of the approved Safe Welding Area. This is not an approved condition.

1) When using SBM or OBM on Hercules 120, the Safe Welding Area will be temporarily decommissioned.
2) When #1 above is in force an appropriate sign designating that the Safe Welding Area is decommissioned/closed will be posted within the decommissioned Safe Welding Area.
3) When #1 above is in force hotwork performed on the rig will be by permit only using the Â¿Chevron Daily Hot Work Permit" process.
4) All hotwork safe practices and procedures as mandated by the approved 'Welding. Burning and Hot Tapping Safe Practices and Procedures Plan' will continue to be adhered to.
